<subSubSection id="C348655EFF97FFF4FF6AFC60FDB38056" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BED36D5FF97FFF4FF6AFC60FDB38056" blockId="5.[151,1437,967,1498]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="B926EAC7FF97FFF4FF6AFC60FED687C6" bold="true" box="[151,274,967,993]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body small to medium, form robust, apterous. Middle ocellus absent, lateral ocelli absent or inconspicuous, with poorly defined. In male, ninth abdominal tergite enlarged, cuculli-form, posterior area obviously divided into 2 spine-shaped lobes, distinctly curved ventrad, emargination between them deep and triangular; subgenital plate without styli, posterior margin with a deep and wide concavity and with apices digitate laterally; cerci short. In female, subgenital plate broad and long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C348655EFF97FFF4FF3AFBDCFC3081FE" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BED36D5FF97FFF4FF3AFBDCFBED8191" blockId="5.[151,1437,967,1498]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="B926EAC7FF97FFF4FF3AFBDCFE8880B2" bold="true" box="[199,332,1147,1173]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Discussion.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC34B24FF97FFF4FEAEFBDCFDDD80B1" author="Liu, X. W. &amp; Yin, H. S." box="[339,537,1147,1174]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" pagination="417 - 418" refId="ref52357" refString="Liu, X. W. &amp; Yin, H. S. (2002) Two new species of Gryllacridinae from China (Orthoptera: Stenopelmatidae). Zoological Research, 23 (5), 417 - 418." type="journal article" year="2002">Liu &amp; Yin (2002)</bibRefCitation>
were firstly reported the 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D56FF97FFF4FCCBFBDCFC7180B2" box="[822,949,1147,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Haglidae" genus="Apotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926EAC7FF97FFF4FCCBFBDCFC7180B2" box="[822,949,1147,1173]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Apotrechus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the Chinese fauna, and the latter authors (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC34B24FF97FFF4FF62FB38FE88809D" author="Liu, X. W. &amp; Bi, W." box="[159,332,1183,1210]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" pagination="11 - 15" refId="ref52567" refString="Liu, X. W. &amp; Bi, W. (2008) Two new species of the genus Apotrechus (Orthoptera: Stenopelmatidae: Gryllacrinae). Entomotaxonomia, 30 (1), 11 - 15." type="journal article" year="2008">Liu &amp; Bi, 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC34B24FF97FFF4FEABFB38FDC1809D" author="Liu, X. W. &amp; Bi, W. &amp; Zhang, F." box="[342,517,1183,1210]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" pagination="53 - 68" refId="ref52607" refString="Liu, X. W., Bi, W. &amp; Zhang, F. (2010) Orthoptera: Stenopelmatoidea. In: Xu, H. C. &amp; Ye, T. X. (Eds.), Insects of Fengyangshan National Nature Rreserve. China Forestry Publishing House, Beijing, pp. 53 - 68." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Liu &amp; 
<emphasis id="B926EAC7FF97FFF4FE62FB38FE78809E" box="[415,444,1183,1209]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">al.</emphasis>
, 2010
</bibRefCitation>
a; Liu &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC34B24FF97FFF4FD99FB38FD16809D" author="Shi, F. M. &amp; Guo, L. Y. &amp; Bian, X." box="[612,722,1183,1210]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" pagination="58 - 68" refId="ref53742" refString="Shi, F. M., Guo, L. Y. &amp; Bian, X. (2012) Remarks on the genus Homogryllacris Liu, 2007 (Orthoptera: Gryllacrididae: Gryllacridinae). Zootaxa, 3414 (1), 58 - 68. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3414.1.4" type="journal article" year="2012">Shi, 2012</bibRefCitation>
; Guo &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC34B24FF97FFF4FCD3FB38FC58809D" author="Shi, F. M. &amp; Guo, L. Y. &amp; Bian, X." box="[814,924,1183,1210]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" pagination="58 - 68" refId="ref53742" refString="Shi, F. M., Guo, L. Y. &amp; Bian, X. (2012) Remarks on the genus Homogryllacris Liu, 2007 (Orthoptera: Gryllacrididae: Gryllacridinae). Zootaxa, 3414 (1), 58 - 68. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3414.1.4" type="journal article" year="2012">Shi, 2012</bibRefCitation>
; Bian &amp; 
<emphasis id="B926EAC7FF97FFF4FC00FB38FBDE809E" box="[1021,1050,1183,1209]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">al.</emphasis>
, 2014; Liu 
<emphasis id="B926EAC7FF97FFF4FB64FB07FB14809E" box="[1177,1232,1183,1209]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">et al.</emphasis>
, 2015a) described 7 Chinese species under 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D56FF97FFF4FE55FB64FDE280FA" box="[424,550,1219,1245]" class="Insecta" family="Haglidae" genus="Apotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926EAC7FF97FFF4FE55FB64FDE280FA" box="[424,550,1219,1245]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Apotrechus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC34B24FF97FFF4FDCEFB64FC9080F9" author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J." box="[563,852,1219,1246]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref45810" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. (2019) A proposal towards classification of the Raspy Crickets (Orthoptera: Stenopelmatoidea: Gryllacrididae) with zoogeographical comments: An initial contribution to the higher classification of the Gryllacridines. Zootaxa, 4605 (1), 1 - 100. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4605.1.1" type="journal article" year="2019">Cadena-Castañeda (2019)</bibRefCitation>
erected the 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D56FF97FFF4FC24FB64FB4780FA" box="[985,1155,1219,1245]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Bianigryllacris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926EAC7FF97FFF4FC24FB64FB4780FA" box="[985,1155,1219,1245]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Bianigryllacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
including all the Chinese species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D56FF97FFF4FEEFFB40FE548126" box="[274,400,1255,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Haglidae" genus="Apotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926EAC7FF97FFF4FEEFFB40FE548126" box="[274,400,1255,1281]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Apotrechus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The genus have obviously difference from 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D56FF97FFF4FC72FB40FBCA8126" box="[911,1038,1255,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Haglidae" genus="Apotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926EAC7FF97FFF4FC72FB40FBCA8126" box="[911,1038,1255,1281]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Apotrechus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in: posterior margin of male ninth abdominal tergite divided into 2 spine-shape lobes, which directing ventrad, between them triangular concave; posterior margin of male subgenital plate with a deep concavity, the lateral lobes digitate apically; female subgenital plate obviously sclerotised without membranous area. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C524D56FF97FFF4FCDBFAF4FC60814A" box="[806,932,1363,1389]" class="Insecta" family="Haglidae" genus="Apotrechus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="206" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926EAC7FF97FFF4FCDBFAF4FC60814A" box="[806,932,1363,1389]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Apotrechus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male ninth abdominal tergite bulbate, apex weakly divided, posterior margin of male subgenital plate projected in the middle, the lateral lobes with or without tubercles apically; female subgenital plate very soft, median area with a soft area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED36D5FF97FFF4FF3AFA18FC3081FE" blockId="5.[151,1437,967,1498]" box="[199,1012,1471,1498]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="B926EAC7FF97FFF4FF3AFA18FE5781FE" bold="true" box="[199,403,1471,1497]" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">Species included.</emphasis>
The genus is endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="F3457645FF97FFF4FD4CFA18FD3081FE" box="[689,756,1471,1497]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="206">China</collectingCountry>
with 8 known species.
</paragraph>
